[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Runtime Platform and Operations Requirements
UID: GHOST-RUNTIME-PLATFORM-OPERATIONS
VERSION: 0.3
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose, Scope, and Status Boundary

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document is the parent requirement specification for the GHOST AWS runtime and operations branch.

It intentionally contains only the deployment-level capability boundaries needed by the documented current AWS system and the approved initial remote MCP extension. Detailed realization belongs in 81_aws_deployment_and_operations.sdoc. Exact environment values belong in 81_aws_deployment_profile.local.md.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AWS Runtime Platform and Operations Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide the runtime-platform and operations capability required to reproduce the documented current AWS deployment and to add the approved initial remote MCP endpoint.

This capability shall be limited to AWS hosting, container execution, image delivery, HTTPS routing, DNS, runtime secrets, persistent AWS runtime data, deployment activation, operational verification, and the MCP deployment boundary.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-PRODUCT-IDENTITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Product and Legacy Deployment Naming
STATEMENT: >>>
The product shall be named GHOST, meaning GenAI Hybrid Orchestrator for Software Tooling.

Existing deployment identifiers containing ragstream may remain as current legacy runtime names until a separately approved migration changes them.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-AWS-ONLY-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AWS-Only Requirement Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
This requirement branch shall contain only requirements that reproduce the documented AWS deployment or realize the approved remote MCP endpoint on that deployment.

It shall not own retrieval, memory, GUI feature behavior, prompt semantics, or any non-deployment capability.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-STATUS-SEPARATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Deployment and Target MCP Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
The documented Streamlit deployment shall be treated as CURRENT.

The MCP extension shall be treated as TARGET until its server code, deployment artifacts, HTTPS route, OAuth interoperability, and client acceptance tests have been implemented and passed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Current AWS Runtime Capability

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The CURRENT requirements describe the user-supplied last-verified AWS deployment and the corresponding current repository deployment artifacts.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-HTTPS-REQUEST-PATH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Public HTTPS Request Path
STATEMENT: >>>
The current public request path shall be Route53 DNS to the EC2 public IPv4 address, then through the EC2 Security Group to nginx on HTTPS port 443, and from nginx to the Dockerized Streamlit backend on host port 8501.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-STREAMLIT-CONTAINER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Streamlit Container Runtime
STATEMENT: >>>
The current human-facing GHOST application shall run as a Docker container on one Ubuntu EC2 instance and shall serve Streamlit on container port 8501.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-IMAGE-DATA-SEPARATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Image and Persistent-Data Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Docker image shall contain application code and runtime dependencies, while the document-ingestion raw files and Chroma database shall remain outside the image on the EC2/EBS filesystem and shall be supplied by bind mounts.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-ECR-DELIVERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Controlled Image Delivery
STATEMENT: >>>
The current delivery path shall build the Docker image in GitHub Actions and push it to the configured private Amazon ECR repository only through the documented manual-dispatch or deploy-marked push conditions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-SSM-SECRET-INJECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current SSM Secret Injection
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 activation path shall obtain the OpenAI API key from AWS SSM Parameter Store at runtime and shall inject it into the application container without storing an AWS access key on the EC2 instance.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-DNS-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Dynamic DNS Activation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 activation path shall read the instance public IPv4 address through IMDSv2 and shall update the configured Route53 A record before the deployment is considered activated.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-CUR-MANUAL-OR-BOOT-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Manual or Boot Activation
STATEMENT: >>>
A newly pushed image shall become active only when the EC2 startup script is run manually or when the enabled systemd service runs that script during instance boot.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. Target Remote MCP Extension

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The TARGET requirements define only the approved deployment boundary for a remote MCP server on the existing EC2/nginx deployment. Functional prompt behavior remains owned by the preprocessing and prompt-functions requirements.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target Separate MCP Container
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial remote MCP server shall run as a container separate from the current Streamlit container on the same EC2 instance.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-HTTPS-ENTRY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target MCP HTTPS Entry
STATEMENT: >>>
The remote MCP server shall be exposed externally only as https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com/mcp through the existing nginx HTTPS entry point.

The MCP backend port shall not be exposed as a public Security Group port.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-LOOPBACK-PROXY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target MCP Loopback Proxy
STATEMENT: >>>
nginx shall proxy the public /mcp route to the MCP container through an EC2 loopback-bound host port so that the connection from nginx to the MCP backend remains local to the instance.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-HTTPS-ENTRY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-TOOL-SCOPE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target MCP Tool Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial MCP server shall expose only the single ghost_engineer_prompt tool defined by 73_mcp_interface.sdoc.

That tool shall reuse the existing deterministic prompt-construction function and then the existing A2 PromptShaper on the same request-isolated SuperPrompt. PreProcessing and A2 shall not be advertised as separate MCP tools.

The MCP server shall not expose document ingestion, document retrieval, reranking, A3, A4, memory, file management, Streamlit control, answer generation, or the full GHOST pipeline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-INTEROPERABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target Claude and ChatGPT OAuth Interoperability
STATEMENT: >>>
The remote MCP endpoint shall use the MCP authorization model for HTTP transports and shall complete authenticated connection and invocation of ghost_engineer_prompt from:

- the owner's ChatGPT web client through its custom MCP plugin capability; and
- Claude through its remote custom connector capability.

Acceptance shall be demonstrated against both real clients rather than inferred only from a local test client or MCP Inspector.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-HTTPS-ENTRY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-STREAMLIT-NONREGRESSION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Target MCP Streamlit Non-Regression
STATEMENT: >>>
Adding or restarting the MCP container shall not replace the current Streamlit container, change the current public root application route, open port 8501 or the MCP backend port publicly, or alter the current document-ingestion bind mounts.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. Ownership and Explicit Exclusions

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section fixes the requirement-file boundaries and prevents unrelated operational or product themes from entering this branch.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-AWS-CHILD-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AWS Child Requirement Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
81_aws_deployment_and_operations.sdoc shall own the detailed current AWS deployment requirements and the detailed target MCP deployment requirements refining this parent capability.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-LOCAL-PROFILE-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Local Deployment Profile Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
81_aws_deployment_profile.local.md shall record exact environment-specific current values, exact current executable deployment artifacts, approved target MCP values, and implementation-assigned target values once those values exist.

The local profile shall contain references and placeholders only for secrets, never secret values.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-RUN-OPS-PHASE1-NONGOALS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Phase-1 Non-Goals
STATEMENT: >>>
The current deployment requirements shall not claim Cognito-driven EC2 auto-start, an Application Load Balancer, CloudFront as an always-on front door, autoscaling, multi-instance operation, or multi-tenant hardening.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[[/SECTION]]
